text: Het Financieele Dagblad (meaning The financial daily newspaper in English; modern spelling: Het Financiële Dagblad) is a daily Dutch newspaper focused on business and financial matters. The paper was established in 1943. The headquarters is in Amsterdam. It was among the newspapers participating in the Panama Papers investigation. ==References== ==External links== * Official website Category:1943 establishments in the Netherlands Category:Business in the Netherlands Category:Business newspapers Category:Dutch-language newspapers Category:Mass media in Amsterdam Category:Daily newspapers published in the Netherlands Category:Publications established in 1943
